Hullo all, thanks to you for replying.<br>
<br>
As it happens, I /petition'd again last evening (CET-time) as I have done for the last couple of days in EQ.<br>
/OOC<br>
<br>
A Guide came to see me last night, asking me for the problem we as a guild were having - I explained to her in detail, in all niceties and flatteries hitherto, that we were without a leader and desperate for something to be done about it.<br>
<br>
OOC<br>
She said she would flag my petition for the GM's and the powers that be to see into it, like someone had done Saturday and Sunday.  I thanked her and went on killing the seafurbies I was hunting - thinking again nothing would come of it.<br>
/OOC<br>
<br>
Not 5 minutes later, a Gnomette of considerable beauty with white hair and the wisdom of ages shining through her misty eyes, asked me to explain once more, in short.<br>
<br>
I did and then a whispering voice told me I had been given leadership ((but I promised that once our MIA leader is back, he will have it again as is his right)).<br>
<br>
So, the GAG is back in business - yeay, cheer, dance.<br>
Gnomish Spirits for everyone!<br>
<br>
OOC<br>
Why not reform the Gnomish Alliance (without the 'of Gnomes') - it would not benefit the acronym - GA instead of GAG - and our guild decided to not disband and restart anew by unanimous vote, so we tried vehemently to get things back in order - which worked...<br>
<br>
Also - a Gnomish Alliance - since Dwarvens are our brethren - distant kin, they too could be in it - that would not be an all-Gnome guild (which is what we try to accomplish).  And we are aligned with the HalfheightHeroes as is - cousins in a cousin guild ;-)<br>
<br>
Thanks once more, and thanks to the GM Gnomette by the name of Naylie  - they make up for some of the negative things they do by doing positive things...<br>
/OOC<br>
